The South African Weather Service says thunderstorms are expected in the Free State, North West, Mpumalanga and KwaZulu-Natal on Sunday.Other parts of the country can expect dry and hot weather conditions, with the mercury soaring up to 35 degrees Celsius.Weather forecaster, Wayne Venter says: As from Tuesday onwards we can expect more thunderstorms to pass over Mpumalanga, as well as KwaZulu-Natal and into Gauteng mainly from Wednesday. -SABC